                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12862103" author="veithen" created="Thu, 29 Apr 2010 06:14:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a real bug because the tests originally worked. There seems to be a problem related to charset encoding in the NHTTP transport.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12862104" author="hiranya" created="Thu, 29 Apr 2010 06:18:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I also ran into a couple occasions where the test suite got hung. Had to stop Maven by hitting ctrl+c.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12862105" author="heshan" created="Thu, 29 Apr 2010 06:19:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After adding the exclusion filter suggested by Hiranya, tests for transport module is passing. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12862139" author="hiranya" created="Thu, 29 Apr 2010 09:07:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There was a problem in RESTUtil class where it removed the original charset encoding value from the content type string before invoking the Axis2 RESTUtil class. I have removed this logic and now all the tests are passing. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please reopen this issue if any regressions are encountered.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
